name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The collection is rich, varied and there is so much to learn and discover…We spent over three hours in the museum and did not even stop to read everything, and neither used the audio guides.
It is my first time in Finland and I have no knowledge of its history and culture. The items and the rooms’ introduction panels gave me many insights without being boring lecture.
Looking forward to its re-opening in 2027!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I was lucky enough to visit the museum before its renovation project began. I can say this place is awesome; there are lots of fascinating collections and interesting things to learn about. Staff was helpful and friendly. Plus, student discount, even when coming from abroad. I am definitely looking forward to visiting again in the near future after expansion is completed.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Visit soon! The museum is to be closed for at least two years due to renovation. The museum houses several permanent exhibitions, including the history of Finland & the pre-historic time on this land. Currently there is also an interesting but temporal exhibition on outsider art, which I highly recommend! The building itself is a classical, elegant architecture, which worths appreciation.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
For 1st-time visitor to Finland, this is a must visit. Especially if you know nothing about the country's past and is keen to find out.

It's a small museum so all you need to spare is a couple of hours.  We went at 4pm on Jan 22, 2023 and it wasn't overly crowded.

Lockers of varying sizes are available to store your belongings. Ticket price was 11€ per person.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This is a very unique museum. It usually takes around 4 hours if you are an art & history enthusiast, other than that 3 hours is probably enough. All the descriptions are available in English and have timeline included. The system is very interactive and you won't get bored. It offers free entry on every Friday fom 4pm-6pm. It's a must visit place in Helsinki.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This museum was really interesting and had lots of history and neat things to see. I highly recommend take a trip to see it. Have free lockers to put your stuff in also. There is a cafe but we didn't eat in it. Looked nice though. Gift shop had some finds for us to bring back.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Truly an amazing museum if you like history and relics from Finland. You have to step away your bags and coats in lockers provided which are free. You can pick up the tokens near the lockers.

The staff are so friendly and their memories are top notch. The displays are great.

Most museums have lots of activities especially for children but adults can have fun too.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Unfortunately there was some construction going on here when I visited Helsinki, but this is a really important landmark for its admirers. First, its beautiful stature and appearance contribute plenty to the Helsinki inside, and the plethora of exhibits inside are equally intriguing, with me specifically recommending the “Story of Finland” if you are into history or just love Finland

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I am not a huge museum fan but i think it is an interesting museum. Many things to see, small text in three languages, and kind of  interactive. I spent almost one and a half hours and saw everything pretty quickly without elaborately reading every caption. I visited it on Friday midday and it was very quiet.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
This is a really great museum worth visiting, especially for tourists who want to learn more about Finland. We had a really good experience by going through chronologically, making sure to start in the basement section on prehistoric Finnish history, moving up through Christian history on the ground floor, and finishing with war and modern history on the higher floors. I think if you missed the bottom or top floors it might feel like an underwhelming experience as the exhibits on the entry level floor are mostly Christian artefacts and paintings - interesting, but best in conjunction with the rest of the museum. The interactive experiences in the prehistoric section were especially good.

Navigating the museum was easy once we actually found where to start - finding the first exhibit was actually really tricky and you had to go through an inconspicuous door through the basement café. The museum could really do with more clearly signing where to go as we felt rather lost a couple of times, even with a map in hand.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: For individuals interested in the Finnish history, mythology and culture, this museum is one of the places to visit. I enjoyed the pre-historic segment of the collection as it was interactive and unique. However, that can't be said about the remaining collections. They were good, but not extraordinary. The museum, however, is user friendly. Visitors can easily work their way through different sections. I would definitely recommend taking the free audio tour. It surely enhanced my understanding while I was going through different sections.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very interesting museum! It’s organized in from prehistoric ages until the present Finland. The exhibits and descriptions were very insightful and especially the past 2 centuries of Finland were depicted very well.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
We only had a couple of hours to see Finland. So my partner recommended this museum as a great option. We both enjoy museums. ,☺ I was very impressed with all the details and different interpretations of languages. They have a cafe downstairs and 2 sets of bathrooms.
The museum was very informative about Finland's history from 1917 to 2017. Could have used a little bit more time but it was a great visit. 👍

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: If you are like me and this is your first visit to Finland, I highly recommend getting to understand the history of the country with a visit to this museum. Great artefacts, some really interesting ways of interacting with some of the exhibits. A lot of effort and care has been put into telling Finland's story here.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It is beautiful building with Finnish history and independence, ice age, middle age, stone age details. Accessible for disabled and kids with strollers.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Haven't been there for many years. Things certainly improved, from exhibition content to the level of service. Worth to spend time with your family or friends.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This museum is really nice. The staffs are really kind and helpful. We were lucky to go there when the computer system did not work. We got in for free! This museum shows the history of Finland with the map and stuffs. It is good for all people to come to learn history. The part that i like the most is you can stand in front of  the mirror, they take a picture of you then your face show up on the painting. Everyone can leave the stuffs in the locker which is really comfortable.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
National Museum of Finland. I spent there  more time ⏲️ than any other museums.
Building for a museum was created by a famous architect, and ots looks like a castle 🏰.
Starting from the basement shows histori from ice ages.
1 floor has exhibition different artists 🎨 and shop with souvenirs.
2 floor has history from Sweden 🇸🇪 protection,  through the Russian empire to present time ⏲️ with independence.
Was interested in catching up on the excursion with early school 🏫 grade where the guide explained who people had lived before.

I can talk about this place a lot, but it's better to go there and see everything by yourself.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I enjoyed my visit here. The museum is a beautiful Art Deco building with pleasant flourishes relating to Finland’s natural history.   The exhibits tell the nation’s story from prehistory, to the arrival of Christianity, to statehood. Worth a visit!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The museum is really nice! With Helsinki card, I didn’t pay for the entrance, it’s included in the card price. The museum staff were really nice and helpful. I lost my Helsinki card while picking up the guide gadget, the staff member found it and returned to me 😇

The museum start with the history of people who lived in Stone Age up to the current days. There was also an exhibition dedicated to Sami people: their lifestyle, clothing. I loved that all.

The coffee in the museum cafe was not great, unfortunately 🙃

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I learned a lot about the history of Finland as it takes you through prehistoric times until the present (Finnish metal bands included). The museum layout was a bit confusing though with no clear idea where to start or how to move around. Went into two exhibitions that led me to the same place.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Quite an interesting museum with many examples of Finalnd's hiatory through the ages. Make sure yiu follow the path and read the informations signs, there are facinating stories.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Nicely organised museum with friendly staff. You can easily spend couple of hours viewing and reading information on exhibitions for the history of Finland. The museum is actually organised in three sectors (one inside each floor): the prehistoric, the swedish-russian, the finish one. All three are interesting but the first and last are the most important as they are the ones more closely related to the pure history of Finland.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great place to learn about the history of Finland and the Finnish people/culture. Try to make this a first stop on a visit to Finland so you have good context for the rest of your visit. The layout of the museum can be somewhat confusing so make sure you navigate the exhibits in the right order. There are plenty of helpful staff on hand - just ask if in doubt. The prehistory and story of Finland sections are really well done. Allow about 2 hours for a visit.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The Finnish National museum is a nice place to visit especially on a rainy or cold day. The permanent collection takes you around the building and gives you a good understanding of the Finnish history and if you do it in a leisurely pace it will take you around an hour. There is also an exhibition about public and hidden Finnish facts and facets, there is also a small exhibition called the arctic spirit displaying Inuit art. Well worth a visit and it is only a 15 minute walk from the central station.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The Finnish National Museum is presenting Finnish history from the Stone Age to the present through objects and cultural history.  It’s located in the center. It’s free on Fridays between 16.00-18.00

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I had a few hours in Helsinki between getting off the ferry from Aland and catching a flight. This was the perfect layover spot. Beautiful building and really interesting exhibits. The bonus was a great lunch buffet in the basement.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: What an interesting place to visit! An interactive and informative journey through Finnish history, starting from the stone age, passing along Swedish and Russian rule, the civil war and WW2. If there is one museum you visit in Helsinki, this should be a top choice.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Amazing museum where you can learn interesting facts about Finnish culture and history. There are also often organised  changing exhibitions so I visit the museum time to time even though I have been there many times. LIFEHACK: You can get to the museum for free every Friday 16-18 or everyday if you are under 18 y.o.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Great museum! Spent a few hours here, well worth the cost of admission. Learned about some of Finland's history while on holiday! At the moment there is a separate Barbie doll exhibit in progress at the museum for an additional admission fee. We didn't feel the need to see this display but it did appear to be popular with others.

Please give me a thumbs up "like" for this review... Thanks!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
This museum offers so much more than its size would suggest. There are lots of sections to wander through to discover the history of Finland from prehistoric times to now.
Take your time to wander through and take it all in. From the history of the sauna to modern heavy metal, you'll find so much to see and do!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Closed on Mondays. I personally didnot like it. Its big but boring. If you have Helsinki card then the entry free. Its takes long time to see everything. I personally don't see anything unique which I will remember. But if you still want to give it a chance then keep this National Museum as last choice to visit.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This is a really wonderful museum!  The exhibitions are very rich, and every corner is exquisite!  Even toddlers will love it

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very impressive museum telling the story of Finland.  Very welcoming staff.  Thank You

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
12 euro entry. only 'free' with the helsinki card.
building is nice, and even has bullet holes from the civil war.
Exhibit is extensive with a timeline from ice age to the present. exhibits themselves are somewhat interactive, and are available in 3 languages including finnish and english.
i felt like it wasn't as easy to follow as some other museums, nothing really wowed us.
charging points and lockers availble, they give u a coin so dont worry about not having cash.
Spent 1.5 hrs here but only managed to see half due to closing.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This very interesting and informative museum was a great place to spend an afternoon, learning about the history of Finland. I enjoyed the interactive exhibits and fun surprises. This museum does a good job of presenting a lot of information in an engaging way.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: So many interesting things to discover, Interactive Finnish history, pre-history, excavations etc... Definitely recommended. Fridays are free between 4-6pm (when i was there in 2021).

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Brilliant place! The exhibitions show the history of Finland from the evangelization by Swedish in 17th century till recent days. The exhibitions are well organized and the narratives are pretty neutral and objective. I even saw criticism on the US’s invasion of Iraq and the notorious operations from the West. It’s a great place to know how Finland survived in the complex geopolitics.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Really nice museum. Visited on the closing night before renovations. Very rich and long collection. Exhibits were interesting and well presented. Layout is a bit confusing at times, though.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Small but encompasses Finland history and the art works of some not so recognized artists.
Beautiful collection.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
This is one of the best museums in Helsinki.
On Fridays in the museum at certain hours there is free admission for everyone.  The museum is usually crowded with people as it is one of the most popular museums.  The museum is located near Kampppi, 10 minutes walk.  The museum is located in a beautiful, historic building.  The exposition is located on several floors.  The building has an elevator, a cloakroom and a café.  There is a children's playroom on the top floor of the museum.  Go barefoot.
The museum also has temporary exhibitions, usually on the ground floor.
I will visit this museum again.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great museum. I really enjoyed my visit. What I liked the most is very interactive with lots of touch screens for a better comprehension. I personally learned a lot. 100% recommendable.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Interesting and educating exhibition about the whole (pre)history of Finland. I especially loved the many interactive installations. Two less stars because the audio guide doesn't have all clips in English and on certain points they spread The Message™. This nonsense has no place in a history museum.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This museum contains some cornerstones of Finnish art as well as occasional paintings from some very famous artists like van Gogh, Cezanne, Gauguin.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Excellent place for any first time visitor to Helsinki. Very good collection of historic artefacts, paintings and various other exhibits.
Sure to keep you enthralled for at least 3 hours.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Interesting museum and building about history of Finland. There was Akseli Gallen-Kallela works exhibition which is really interesting. I have visited before, maybe 20 yrs ago. Should go more often since content change. Friday at 4pm admission is free.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It's a super nice museum. The exhibition system is well organized. It will be enlarged to the underground part in the future. I am looking forward to coming again and visiting the new part.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Excellent National museum. The Prehistory exhibit is among the best I've seen anywhere in the world.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Went with my bath mates,
Amazing experience, must visit atleast for once.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The Barbie exhibition was surprisingly good! There are so many dolls, some of them dressed by designers, others for movies and specisl occasions. They are really beautiful. They also offer a "buddy" Barbie for kids to take along and Barbies tonbuy in the gift shop. The exhibition is really popular, so expect a lot of people!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Some exhibits had an accent on transformations and visuals which I found really exciting. You can definitely find some extraordinary stuff there!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Exhibitions were nicely themed, many interactive exhibits. You can learn a lot about Finland's history and customs.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great place, unfortunately it will be able for visiting next time after three years.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A very educational museum, showing the history of Finland. It is an important place to learn about the Finnish heritage, history and culture.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Nice place to get lost for several hours. You can touch some exhibits (dream come true), use free audio guide and enjoy multimedia support. And they have a collection of mittens, how cute is that!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: One of the most interactive museums i have ever been, it was a real pleasure and lots of things to discover!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Arguably the best museum I have visited.  Carefully designed layout and content generates interest and informs on  Finland's distant and recent past. Will definitely be back.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This is an excellent history museum, stretching from pre-history to the present. The museum is well-designed, save for one disconnect (after the pre-history section, walk to the left through the collection to get to the beginning of the medieval period). There are ample English explanations that provide the historical context of each rooms’ artifacts. Recommend this to be the first stop on a trip through Helsinki.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: We went there to learn more about Finnish history and bright, it's a lot! The exhibition starts in the Stone Age and goes all the way to present-day Finland. The exhibition is very interactive and therefore fun. I also really like the fact that there are free audio guides. You can spend several hours there.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Omg I so loved it! All the Epoches of finnish History, just great! And on Friday 16-18:00 for free

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Nice tour to the past culture of Finland. You can come up with your own slogans for Finland which once approved will be set in the public display.

4 story building which is still being expanded to accomodate more.

A must visit if you are keen about knowing Finland.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It is a good museum with history that spans from the first settlers to the modern time. But I was hoping for more medieval weapons and not much stuff in general.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Worth the visit if you have 2-3 hours to kill and want to understand Finnish history.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A beautiful museum; this place makes for an afternoon well spent. The current Homecoming exhibit on repatriation of Sami artifacts is particularly worth seeing, especially the way that they've approached showing the artifacts. 10/10

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Located on an old castle, you can walk Finland history from the early stone age until today. Very well presented. Is a high quality museum. The restaurant with its buffet is all tipical, tasty and cheap

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great place to visit specially on Friday evening (4 to 6 pm) when there is free entry.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Love this huge museum, every details are taken care off. Staffs are nice as well

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Nice museum where it goes from early stonage to vikings all the way to this day and age. Explains a lot bout Finnland and its traditions

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A place to learn about the history of Finland. Quite a bit of artifacts in exhibition. Definitely worth exploring.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The attic is lovely to visit with small kids. They were entertained for over 2h while learning. The permanent and temporary exhibitions are good and with explanations in English, Swedish and Finnish. It is one of the nice museums in Helsinki and the building is beautiful.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great place to learn more about Finland’s history! Well made with interactive and fun activities to keep you engaged. We went in after 4pm on a Friday so the admission was free.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Expensive compared to other things you could do that take a similar amount of time - but we still found it interesting, and are happy we went. Good variety of things to see, and especially enjoyed the interactive photo bits.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: My favourite museum in Helsinki. Many interactive activities to learn about history. Free admission on Friday

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The National Museum of Finland is located in the central of Helsinki. This is a place where you can learn the history from the stone ages to nowadays. The descriptions are in Finnish and English ... And may be also in Swedish. So, as a traveller, I am able to enjoy the Finnish History!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Really great museum! Remember to take a map and the free audio guide :)

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Only spent 2 hours because we arrived late but we have enjoyed it a lot. I am mostly interested in pre medieval history and the displays regarding that time frame were interesting.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I really enjoyed it, very nice and comprehensive excursus from prehistoric times to modern era

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very comprehensive exhibits sharing such a lot about the history of Finland. Excellent!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great museum to see and explore. Offers a wide variety of information and interaction using technology to create an extremely immersive and educational experience.  Worth the visit!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Totally loved it and highly recommend to include in your itinerary. About 100 to 200 meters from Nationalmuseum tram station. Ticket is 16 euro including a locker facility to safely keep your belongings.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: One of the must when in Helsinki. Get to this museo and learn about Finland’s history and amazing exhibitions!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
I thought long and hard about why I disliked this museum so much. The reason: it is aimed at the worst possible demographic, the educated normie. Nothing wrong with normies, the Danish museum of Moesgaard, which has a very similar concept for example, is also aimed at them. The good thing moesgaard does though, is that it still tells a full story that not only builds on known concepts in Danish history, but also explains the fundamentals. Here is where this museum goes completely square.

I walk into an exhibition about prehistoric Finland, and there are some interesting exhibition pieces. Instead of explaining what we know about the Finnish prehistory however, the exhibition decides to wax lyrically about why Bishop Henry never existed and he was never martyred because there are no contemporary written sources about it, and in the same breath writes in detail about the practically undocumented Finnish religion, where suddenly, relics, tradition and etymology are enough to establish its veracity. Finally, I was excited to find interesting views on the winter war, and my wife to get to know the basics for it, and that monumental figure of Finnish history, Mannerheim. At this point unsurprisingly, the winter war is only mentioned, outside of chronological order, on one single wall with some uninteresting pictures.

Here again comes into the picture the educated normie. He knows what the winter war is. But what does he not know, this rootless cosmopolitan? What the Sami and women did. The museum goes on and on about this, not at all addressing the cause and walk of the conflict, leaving us completely bewildered, this being Finlands greatest hour. Mannerheim is only mentioned twice, both as a side note in a larger picture when he was twice responsible for, in every sense of the word, the survival of Finland. This to me almost seems like the administrators of this museum seem to think of this era as shameful.

The only parts I found laudable were the detail on recent history, and the collection of prehistoric objects. Apart from that it is a museum focused on platitudes, pandering to its international demographic and some sort of faux intellectualism, which one can smell from a million miles away. It goes on and on about the meaning of history, but fails to tell it. all in all, while we did not regret our visit my review is mainly to signify that it could be many many times better, and that it's shameful it is not for there is rarely a nation that has achieved more during its short existence, and its worth learning about.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A very good exhibition about the history of Finland, from the prehistoric times till today. It won’t take more than 2 hours and on Friday during the last two hours is actually free.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Good work of showing the path of Finland history and Helsinki. Thank you.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: One of the most balanced museums among those I've ever seen. Tells a lot about nation-building in quite neutral and academic sense.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The moomin exhibit was good. I'd have loved to see more about the TV series that I used to watch as a child. However, I saw many kids enjoying the place.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I would not miss this one when visiting Helsinki. Very interesting, learned a lot about the history and cultures of Finland.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Important part of Finnish history and always smaller exhibitions of special subjects

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This place is very unique and very grand. It fits as a perfect place for families to visit and learn about Finnish history and culture together and enjoy the time. It has a lot of interesting places and it is vast with different things you must see.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The Finnish National Museum is certainly worth a visit. It is not at all dull or dusty - it's full of interesting exhibitions and interactive installations. Also kids are welcome and there's always special activities for them.
The architecture and art  you can experience in the museum is phenomenal.
The cozy café serves lunch, good coffee, refreshments, pastries and other delicacies for small hunger.
The service is friendly and helpful. Brochures in many languages are available.
Highly recommended.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: We loved visiting this museum every few years, and it provides excellent information about Finland's history (and we love Finland!). The rotating exhibit with the non-traditional art was really good. The historical displays were fantastic. The lockers were very convenient, and they provided tokens for their operation. If you like Finland, this is a great way to learn more about it.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Excellent museum! They have done a good job with the displays and the history. I felt enlightened both by the Finnish history and the historic facts in general. I had just under two hours here, and that was a bit short. I highly recommend this museum.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Small museum, there was a lot of attention paid to South American history,  barely anything about Viking and Finland history.  Rare Ulfberht sword had no mention of significance.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Definitely a must stop if you want to learn more about Finland and the Finnish people.  I easily spent two hours inside, and could have easily spent a third hour had I read every placard.  The history of Finland was fascinating.  Everything was well documented in both Finnish and English.  There is also an audio portion that is available in several languages, and content for children as well.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Really beautiful building and lots to see.  A bit confusing timeline but exhibits are explained well and there’s a little cafe and shop too.  Trams stop right in front but not far from city centre.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very good museum went there to see the newest exbition and there was a very good presentation of incas and the history behind them.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Totally and utterly boring.  It only concentrated on the recent growth of Helsinki.  The only interesting part was where they showed a flat from the 1950's.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Really enjoyed the museum! Didn’t know a lot about the history of Finland before deciding to come to visit the country. The museum provided a great crash course!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Learnt some interested fact about Finland. For example, they are crazy of sauna. And they have been influenced in last century by the Soviet.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Amazing place where the history is presented using modern technology. If you want to see and interact with everything there plan to stay there for the whole day!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Smaller then expected, but you will gain a good understanding of Finlands history.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Must-Go, if you are history lover to know a country here Finland. Easy to access, not boring place.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Wonderful museum in Helsinki about Finland history.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very interesting museum & exhibits. Learnt lots about Finland that despite having visited the country for the last 20 years, I did not know about.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: As an American looking for an understanding of the Finnish people and their history, this museum was disappointing. It was disjointed with vignettes on a host of topics that were not well tied together and many of which were not easily understandable or related to the history of Finland.   Helsinki is gorgeous and Finland is an interesting country but there are better ways to spend your time.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The museum itself is fine, although I'd have liked more information on Finland's road towards independence.

What I really don't understand is why it is 2 euros cheaper to buy the ticket online instead of at the museum desk (especially since there was no line). I bought my ticket online in the end but it seems a bit pointless and also annoying for people who don't have internet / are not so handy with their phones.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great museum and we really enjoyed it. The information is in Swedish, Finnish, and English and they offer translation devices for a guided tour experience. You can also download the app to your phone and use it instead.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Very interactive, there were differently themed floors, I especially enjoyed the prehistorical exhibition. There is a nice museum café, with very fair prices and good apple pie. Lockers (and the tokens for them) available.
There will be maintenance for several months coming soon, so it is bound to change.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great storytelling from the stone age to Golden Age of finish Heavy Metal. A lot of multimedia, quite a bit of interactivity, all in a chilled atmosphere that lends itself to hours of study, contemplation or interaction.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Interesting museum with tons of artefacts about Finnish history, would recommend warmly for any visit to Helsinki.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Fresco-disco highly recommend. Staff overall was super friendly and helpful.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Just spent a whole afternoon and felt spiritually contented afterwards.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: My favorite museum I've been to in Finland so far!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Good place to know Finland history

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A very interesting museum. It was open on Monday which was nice because not much was. Some great educational parts which I learned from a bit. Overall a great place to go on your first trip to Finland.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Good exhibits, signs and information written in English so easy to understand for a tourist. Big collection with plenty to kill a good 1-2 hours. Mixture of art, modern era and historical items and a good overview of Finland and it's past. I especially liked the section covering Finnish saunas and why they are such an important part of the culture. Very expensive but I'm spoiled as most countries I've been to national museums like this are either free or quite cheap.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very nice museum with the History of Finland. Free with Museum Card. Not very busy on a Sunday afternoon. Worth the visit.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Good museum and experience. Be careful: CLOSED ON MONDAY! The National museum should be opened every day. Many tourist were out of the museum on Monday expecting the opening.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
I was disappointed in the museum.

First I realised that tickets were cheaper online and me and the cashier spent ages trying to make the website work to purchase them online to save a few euros. We ended up giving up after 5 mn because the website is not user friendly nor responsive

Then it was quite difficult to follow the timeline and know in which rooms to start. I got lost many times and sometimes had to go back on my feet to find the exit.

After doing the museum I still don't have a precise idea of finlands history. There was a mix of history, geography and culture. I did like the part on the maternity package and the sauna but the rest was a bit random. For instance at the end there is a chronology where Finnish events and general historical facts are mixed and we don't really see the connection.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: This was my second time in 3 tears visiting the museum, it’s absolutely a must for a person trying to integrate into Finnish society and get to know Finns. Did you know fishnet is the oldest thing they found in Suomen maa? Did you know they used squirrel fur for so long as a trading buffer? Did you know the first “artistic” object found in Suomi is an elk head out of wood which was attached to a bothand it just looks lien the seed from ice age? I didn’t

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very unusual museum. It is a small museum but has enough things to look. A bit scary atmosphere.  Try and u will feel.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The museum was nice, but really confusing to go around, I would really wish for more clear guidance. And also, one whole floor was not open, and that sadly didn't come up before paying for our tickets. But overall, really nice.

I heard how one worker said with really rude voice not to touch things, it's understandable yes, but they could be friendlier with their tone. (Tho ofc, i don't know if they had reminded about this earlier and the person continued touching)

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A must visit for visitors to Helsinki, the National Museum of Finland is an ancient building that houses the history of a magnificent and lovely nation.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
The section on the stone age to the iron age is really good - interactive and informative.
The staff is also really friendly.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
A letdown. There was barely anything about the parts of Finnish history I was really interested to learn about (involvement in WWII, Winter War, Sámi culture). We only had a few hours in Helsinki and regret coming here. We should have taken the boat to the military museum instead but assumed this museum would give us a better picture of overall history. Unfortunately the presentation of artifacts is quite uninteresting which I don't think is down to the collection, rather the choice of audience they have tried to cater to. The layout of the museum is also confusing and anachronistic.

It could be that I've been spoiled by other high quality European national museums such as those in Latvia, Czechia and Estonia. We spent two hours here and found it quite flat and unmemorable.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The exhibitiom is a little bit chaotic and for me dissapointing. I expected more info about the ancient times but actually most of the exhibitions are devoted to the newer era (since 17th century).

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Fantastic Museum - worth visiting for sure. Gives a great overview of Finnish history. There are some interactive features, and the museum has a good flow which is easy to follow.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Amazing place recomed all people who traveling in the Helsinki

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Nice permanent collection on the past of Finland. The temporary exhibit was very good as well.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Life before wars and religion. So simple an peaceful. Museum gives a great overview of history in the area and why finnish people are like they are.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The best museum I’ve been to. Except the Muumi Museo in Tampere. But Finnish National Museum is one of a kind. Whole Finland, nationality, freat finnish people in one place. It’s a hot spot on the map for everyone visiting the best country in the world.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Loved the snarky Finnish comments. Like: "our flag was a rush job done in 4 hours. Person hired to do it resigned after parliament changed the design".

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
This museum is beautiful and has so many fantastic exhibits. There is so much to learn about Finnish culture, its impact on the world, and how the Finnish people have survived for hundreds of years.
The staff were also very professional, very courteous.
I was also very impressed by the localizations; how you can experience and learn from the museum in Finnish, Swedish, English, or Russian.
I would absolutely go again.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Amazing place! Great collection!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: the texts are a bit cumbersome, at least for children it is useless in my opinion, children usually seek to interact with things because the few readings they find are very complicated for them.  Unless they go with a guide or with good-souled parents for the museums.  I just want to remind you that children are the future. In the area of ​​the swords, there is a very boring video that I assumed was to show how they used the weapons, I kept watching and the video felt like an eternity.  It should have been more accurate and more accelerated.  people cannot spend 10-15 minutes standing still just watching a video of a child walking around.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Worthy visit to the general collection that helps learning and understanding a bit more about the country. The Muumin expo is very recommended with kids but it was a bit crowded.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Surprisingly fun!
This is an amazing museum.
What surprised me most was how child-friendly of a place it is, with interactive exhibits well designed to inspire curiosity in children, and offers something interesting for each level of of childhood maturity and understanding. It's not just a stuffy ark, nor a simple repository of relics, but should indeed inspire inquisitive people of all ages. Must be experienced in person for the full effect. Accessable in many languages, lively, surprising, delightful, inspiring, sometimes gay, sometimes spooky, I cannot but recommend this museum very highly.
Many exhibits are designed to appeal to Helsinki residents, others to the local people of Uusimaa, or to all Finnic peoples generally, including those in Northern Ural and Siberia, while others still appeal to the common history of all Hanseatic peoples of the Baltic. It's a craftwork museum, dedicated to the ingenuity Finnish minds both prehistoric and modern. It's oddly also a museum of ancient Roman Trade, obliquely, when it's not tangentially a museum of Scandic Heritage or is glancing askance of Slavic Tradition, all on which are obviously on display inexplicitly. What cannot be missed, because zero room is left to doubt, is the empirical explication of the history of the strength of the Finnish Peoples in the face of so much unfathomable adversity, and the museum stands as an attestation of Sisu in the face of competing empires. Take your time and contemplate each item, carefully chosen to display, and how! It's an experience ranging from ancient mythology and lore to 19th Century courtly finesse and regal refinements. It's a museum of hardship, sorrow, ethnographic endurance, and ultimately victory, full of fear and dispair; courage and hope. Don't sleep on this one.
It's truly an excellent, fun experience.
And unlike the rest of the city, the coffee wasn't burnt.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The National Museum is a great short trip in Helsinki, with a interesting set of exhibits from over a millennium of life in Finland, from before it was a country, to it's various rulers and post independence. Well worth a visit, and entry is free!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
It's quite ok for the tour. There are some points that you can interact with the  photos or paintings. The museum covers most of the time periods of Finland.
I just don't like the experience with the staff here. When I walked with my partner to look around in a quiet room, there was a staff coming from behind us and suddenly spoke out loud:" sir n madame, do you have ticket?" I were quite shock, because I never experienced this ticket check like this in any other Finnish museum. He could quietly look at our shirt to check the ticket sticker or gently ask us. Why he had to impolitely speak like shouting and check the ticket like in a tram/bus? I showed him the sticker on my shirt. Then he spoke something loudly (but not clear English and under the mask) to us (like tour guide for an exhibition wall in the room), then he left. I (as lived in Finland for 10 year) and my Finnish partner just looked at each other and could not understand what was just happening.
We did not need staff guidance in museum exhibition room if not in need or not in a guided tour trip.  The museum should have a staff at the entrance to to check the ticket, not at the middle of the museum and don't disturb the visitors.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Definitely worth a visit. There are interesting information, history, and stories from prehistoric Finland to 20th century. I always like to see the timelines, how one place is developing in relation to other parts of the world. There are interesting maps from 1100s where Finland had first appeared on the maps. I especially liked the reconstruction of a woman's outfit from findings. There are free audio information however they could be more of them. The prehistoric part was over emphasized, I missed the big picture of Finnish history, I think Tuku castle has a much better info on history of Finland. Overall it was interesting.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I went here to see the collection of Tom of Finland which was highlighed on the website, but I couldn't find it. I didn't have time, so I may have missed it. The presentation is very good. The entrance fee is correct. If you're interested in Finnish history, this is a good place to spend time.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Probably the most interesting museum there in the city. So many interesting stuff, from swords to thrones and pianos. A must in my opinion.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It's interesting when you see something before milloin years and that what you can see there

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Small but very interesting museum where you can learn a lot about Finland history: the great war, middle ages, even prehistoric period. Well organized, facilities and exhibitions in mint condition. Smart interactions, not only for children but for everybody. Staff is extremely friendly and helpful. Shop may be a little bit expensive but it offers interesting crafts. Plan 2-3 hours for your visit. Loved it.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Good museum where you can spend 1.5 to 2 hours. 15 euros entrance fees
Quite interesting content, some entertaining rooms where you can take a picture of yourself to see them reflected in the room. Give it a try if you have time in your schedule

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Great museum, lots to do and see

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Nice museum in a very beautiful building. Follows the history of Finland from the middle ages to the more modern times.

Just be careful to take the tour in the right direction (starting from the entrance opposite the front desk). Otherwise, like us, you risk getting confused about the timeline continuity of the different plaques...

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It has a nice structure and flow, with three sections to permanent exhibition;: prehistoric, medieval and modern. Its quite small so you can get around fast and it's a nice collection of pieces.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Good museum, lots of really cool interactive things. I do wish there was more explanation of the history of Finland though.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: We'll organized and tells Fimlad's story well.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Top class museum set in a beautiful building. Several interesting exhibitions meant we spent over 3 hours here. Feel like I understand Finland a bit more now! Highly recommend.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: beautiful and informative museum! bit awkward to navigate but maybe the renovation under the dome got us confused😁 especially liked the "president of the future" part.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The National Museum of Finland is one of the most organized and interactive museums of this kind that I have visited in Europe, with a precise and truthful storyline from the prehistoric age to current days. It is very interesting to see an unbiased exhibition, showcasing both the boom periods and the downturns, including the natural, political or economic reasons that lead to them. The museum has different interactive areas, with up-to-date technologies. I highly recommend a visit during the stay in Helsinki.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Fantastic experience. It's is the kind of museum that I appreciate the most and people who organise the display made a great job of getting the essence of long interesting history of Finland. There are not many paintings but some rare pieces are on display. The stuff is mixed from room to room to keep you alert - memorabilia, militaria, art, crafts, religion etc. Free audio guide if you want. Some interactive stuff. I suggest to spend more than 3 hours, if you have less then rush a little. It is hard to feel the size of the museum (it's larger then the man at info kiosk explained). Ps. For some reason they hate backpacks there. The staff buggered me about my backpack a couple of times.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: An excellent place to spend a couple of hours, lots to see and learn about Finland

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The museum itself is so-so, but it's soon to undergo a thorough modernization. However, I am saddened by the unnecessary slaughter of old trees in the back courtyard.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: One of the most interesting and well-designed museums I've ever been to.  It's intellectually challenging and engaging, but the displays function more as a series of thought-provoking deep dives related to Finnish culture as opposed to a relaxed general overview of historical events, so visitors with lots of museum experience should go with that in mind.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A nice museum but a staff at front desk was extremely rude. We had started to wander up the stairs (without knowing that a ticket was required to go up the stairs to the balcony area, not knowing there were exhibits upstairs) when she yelled at us and while we were apologetic and obviously willing to buy the tickets, she was extremely aggressive and rude. Ruined the whole experience.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It is aimed at Finnish citizens. There are cards in English everywhere, so i could understand the displays. I only downgrade because, to be honest, I don't plan to make effort to retain information of their history.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Japanese performance is free every day. Very interesting collection. Also, you can see many interesting collections of dress, cups, bikes, digital objects.
The national museum also you can visit free on Friday from 4.00- till 6.00 p.m.
If you want to pay, you can visit every day. But I think it is better to visit free than pay money because it is not so cheap, around 15 euro.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The National Museum of Finland should definitely be on your to do list if you are visiting Helsinki. The exhibits show casing the history is made interesting by some of the interactive installations such as VR, AR etc. If you are interested in history to cover each and every part of the museum you will spend around 2-3 hours.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: An interesting place that can give you a glimpse of finland's past. The best thing about this plays is that the information us presented in a dynamic and modern wat so you can really relate and take an active part in some of the exhibitions.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Excellent museum to learn about Finnish history. I loved the displays. For researches. I recommend their archive for doing research on national folk costumes. The archivists were friendly and helpful.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: The museum has a confusing structure and lacks sings to direct you in the right way. These make it difficult to walk around and see everything that the museum has to offer. Oh btw, keep in mind that on Fridays between 16-18 o'clock, it's free to enter.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Awesome museum. Nice installations and solid historical collections. Definitely a must go for anyone who wants to get to know more about Finland

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Some very interesting exhibits, particularly the one on the waterlogged mass grave of women and children (basement). Some cool interactive elements, possibly more for children than adults. A fairly solid museum, but lacking exhibit cohesion and thematic arrangements. Kind of "a little of this, a little of that" throughout.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: One of the most ponderable museum, and attraction in general, in Finland. In several section visitor is guided through steps of history of Finland worth mentioning from ice age through last years' events. Exhibitions are well implemented and traditional and modern technological methods have been combined in a good manner. There is a changing exhibition as well, and also occasionally possibility to climb up the building tower. The museum also has a cafeteria and premises for organising seminars and smaller gatherings.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very nice museum about finnish history. Beginning from the stone age in an exhibition at the cellar of the museum, the museum covers the last 10.000 ages and finally culminates in the present age at the 2nd floor. A current exhibition is available for free at the ground floor and is about findings of cultural objects in south- and central America.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: I've visited this museum many times since childhood. Beautiful building and always something interesting to see.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Such a disappointment. With the exception of the prehistoric exhibition, which is great, they've changed almost everything in the last 3 years. Most of the ancient exhibition, most of the paintings, artefacts and folk costumes are gone. From the prehistoric part you enter directly into the Renaissance and them into the modern era. With very few things to see. Too bad. It use to be such a nice museum. Fortunately I still have the photos with the past exhibition!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: It was really nice experience to visit that museum after more then 3 decades break. Unfortunately part of museum is closed for renovation now, but there was interesting exhibition of Inka- and other American cultures.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: A very well maintained museum..The building too is pretty well maintained and is historic..The museum has lots to offer to the one who is keen to know the history! Perfectly placed with Parliament building right next to it, n Helsinki Music centre right opposite!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
One of the must visit if you arrive in Helsinki , a very interactive museum , me and my family enjoyed 2-3 hours of history of finland 🇫🇮......
Really Nice staff

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Nice museum if you into history. €14 little bit on the higher end. good public transport links. walking distance to the Temppeliaukio Church.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Loved it. An interactive museum experience about finish culture and history. Nice building, helpful staff. More than 2 hours should be spend on. Worth its admission cost.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Lovely place, as a foreigner, it gives you so many answers to Finland particular traits. I definitely recommend it and save at least 3 hours to enjoy it

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: They have made yr visit interestingly interactive. Spent almost 2 hours here and still didn't see everything. Will have to go back. Informative and fun!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Not bad, pretty comprehensive although it can feel hard to relate to Finnish history if one is not Finnish

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Beautiful building, exhibits are worth the admission.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Very ambitious in scope, they include history, culture, social changes, and arts. Definitely worth a visit.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
先史時代から現代まで、考古学的な遺物や様々な文化史料を展示しているフィンランドの国立博物館。建物はそこまで大きくもないが古代の石器に始まり、中世, 近世, 近代, 現代と複数階層にわたって多くの遺物を展示しており、大変見応えがある。展示の説明文は英語もあるのでフィンランド語やスウェーデン語が分からなくとも読むことができる。
建物自体も1910年頃の建物でこれもある種の文化財と言えるかもしれない。

公式サイトによると2024年9月現在休館中で、2027年春に再開予定とのこと。

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Ihana aarrekammio. Niin paljon historiaa, niin kauniissa paikassa. Oli upeaa nähdä, monella eri tavalla, miten esi-isämme ovat eläneet ja elantonsa saaneet. Nyky tekniikkaa oli käytetty hienosti havainnollistamaan eri tapahtumia. Hetken aikaa luulin, että nyt sekosin, kun entiset ja nykyisen presidenttien silmät alkoivat räpsyä ja ilmeet vaihtua. Erittäin jännä ja hauska kokemus. Kuinkahan hieno Suomen kansallismuseo onkaan laajan remontin jälkeen. Kannattaa käydä nyt ja sitten myös remontin jälkeen.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Interessante museo della storia Finlandese, usufruito del festival dei musei by night visitandolo la sera del 17 Agosto. Qui abbiamo potuto vedere una mostra artistica che non ci ha particolarmente coinvolto, ma il resto ci è piaciuto maggiormente. Costo molto alto per visitarlo, sui 16€. Ad ogni modo abbiamo imparato qualcosa di più di questa giovane nazione.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Loistava museokokonaisuus. Kertoo upeasti Suomen historiaa eri aikakausilta. Moderneja tekniikoita käytössä ja esineitä pääsee näkemään hyvin läheltä. Huoneita ja kerroksia on paljon eli varaa kunnolla aikaa jos aiot nähdä kaiken kerralla.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Musee très intéressant et qui permet de mieux comprendre l'histoire du pays. Un peu compliquée de comprendre l'organisation des salles au début. Le lieu est magnifique.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Suomen historiasta ja vähän nykyisyydestäkin kertova monipuolinen museo erittäin kauniissa rakennuksessa, aivan muiden kaupungin nähtävyyksien vieressä
Näyttelyssä on hyödynnetty paljon myös nykytekniikkaa.
Paikassa on myös kahvila.
Aukioloaika voisi olla hieman pidempi (-18 nyt) ainakin kesäisin.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: 偶然閉館の最終日に訪れました。翌日からは閉まって向こう3年は工事で閉館するみたいです。ギリギリ入れてよかったです。最終日だったので人も多く無料で入れました。

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Premetto che non amo visitare musei e anche in questo caso non ho fatto eccezione. Soprattutto non sono intenzionato a visitarli se non so già cosa aspettarmi e la cosa si acuisce se sono a pagamento. Quindi ho scelto di non entrarci. Posso quindi solo dare un giudizio personale sull'esterno che ricorda più una chiesa protestante (probabilmente prima lo era?) che un museo. Anzi, tengo per me anche il giudizio estetico visto che di solito mi dicono di avere gusti discutibili, ma sbagliano di grosso e lo sanno.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Musée présentant l'histoire et la culture de la Finlande. Accueil sympathique. Pas trop grand mais bien présenté dans un cadre mettant en valeur les collections de manière moderne. Prévoir environ deux heures pour une visite complète, ou même plus si affinités pour l’histoire.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Upea museo pienen kävelymatkan päässä Helsingin ydinkeskustasta, Eduskuntatalon vieressä. Jo rakennuksen piha on upea.

Aulasta kulku kauppaan, missä on monipuolisesti tavaroita. Aulan katosta ohessa videomateriaalia. Kuvia voisi ottaa täältä vaikka kuinka paljon, arvostelun mukana vain pari hassua.

Lapset hienosti huomioitu kolmannen kerroksen lasten osiolla.

Ehdottomasti käymisen arvoinen! Jokaiselle jotakin!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Upea rakennus ulko- ja sisäpuolelta♥️
Kerroksia oli kolme.
Ylimmässä oli työpaja, toisessa Suomen historiaa käsittelevä näyttely (+näyttely jota uudistettiin ja joka avataan vasta 2021) ja ensimmäisessä kerroksessa vaihtuva näyttely sekä kauppa.
Vaihtuvana näyttelynä oli "Maailma jota ei ollut" , joka kertoo Väli -ja Etelä-Amerikan muinaisista kulttuureista.
Näyttely oli hyvin rakennettu ja mielenkiintoinen.
Siellä oli paljon esineitä eri aikakausilta.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Hyvä museo jossa monenlaista nähtävää. Nyt 16.10.2023 menee korjauksen alle niin avautuu vasta vuonna 2027

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
تتصدر هلسنكي العاصمة قائمة تلك المناطق التي تشتمل على كافة مقومات الجذب السياحي.

متحف فنلندا الوطني
تأسس في عام 1912 ، ويعرض ذلك المتحف الوطني الفنلندي للتاريخ الفنلندي الغني بتاريخ البلاد . متحف فنلندا الوطني مبني على الأسلوب الرومانسي الوطني ، والهندسة المعمارية الخلابة . القلعة القديمة تحافظ على مجموعة واسعة من الاكتشافات الأثرية ، فضلا عن التحف التاريخية والثقافية . وجاء قسم ما قبل التاريخ في المتحف بإعتبارها أكبر تجميع لمواد علم السلوك في البلاد . على مر السنين ، يستضيف المتحف للمهرجانات والمعارض الشهيرة حيث يمكن للزوار التعرف على مدى تطور الثقافة الفنلندية باستخدام المهام التفاعلية .

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Kävin museossa heinäkuussa 2022. Lipunmyynti oli tehty varsin sujuvaksi aulan keskellä. Laukut sai laitettu itsepalvelukaapiin, joka nyt oli ilmainen. Aika vähän kaappeja eli tuuria on jos saa kaapin.
Tilat olivat valoisat. Hiukan olisin kaivannut enempi opasteita mutta kierroksen sain tehtyä.
Esillelaitto on tehty ilmavasti ja raikkaasti . Hyvän kuvan sai Suomen historiasta. Alakerran ravintolasta saa vatsantäytettä.
Lipun pystyy ostamaan netistä myös ennakkoon.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: J'ai adoré le plafond offre une coupole peinte qui est magnifique...des expositions très intéressantes et bien expliquées et des guides très sympathiques....certains parlent même le Français...Je recommande vivement même avec des enfants

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Jykevä, upea rakennus kattomaalauksineen ja taidelasi -ikkunoineen. Mielenkiintoisia vaihtuvia näyttelyitä pysyvien lisäksi.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Lähdettiin pohjoisesta katsomaan kotikaupungin taiteilijan valokuvanäyttelyä. Jaakko Heikkilän näyttely Vaurauden filosofia oli hyvin opastettu, kiitos oppaalle. Suosittelen opastuksia, ne avaavat taustoja. Ja saa myös kysyä.
Kiersimme samalla perusnäyttelynkin. Schaumanin paita ja Gallen-Kallelan lippuehdotukset to see -listalla. Museokauppa oli käymisen arvoinen myös.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Helsinkipäivän satoa...
Täysin uusi tuttavuus, mutta ehdottomasti kannatti käydä. Edelleen museokortti rohkaisi tähän, mutta pääsymaksullekin saa taatusti vastinetta.
Hyvin organisoitu, monipuolinen ja viihdyttäväkin kokemus.
Suosittelen varauksettomasti.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Loistava museokokonaisuus. Ajallinen syvyys itse rakennuksen ja sen tarjoaman miljöön osalta hyvin vaikuttava. Hieno Saamelais-kulttuurin näyttely parhaillaan.
Pysyviin museon näyttelyihin tutustuminen vaatii vielä toisen käynnin. Vaatetuksen ja kassit sai kätevästi tallelokeroon kiertelyn ajaksi. Hieno museokauppa, jossa oli vaikutteita museon teemoista. Kahvilakin löytyi ja katseltavaa useassa kerroksessa. Ylhäällä museoituja leluja ja leikkitila lapsille.
Suomen lähihistorian osuus ja "tulevaisuuden museo" myös mielenkiintoisia teemoja. Suosittelen varaamaan aikaa ja käymään täällä.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Замечательный музей, много интерактива, много интересного, есть отличный лайфхак, в пятницу с 16 до 18 вход в музей свободный, это очень радует, когда не нужно расставаться со своими кровными.  Здесь вы сможете целиком познакомиться с историей Финляндии от и до. Что действительно поражает это наличие разной техники, экранов, галограм и всякого всякого. Что сказать, рекомендую, посетите не пожалеете!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Mielettömän hieno paikka. Hienosti toteutetut näyttelyt, paljon nähtävää ja kuultavaa. Täällä vierähtää tovi jos toinenkin. Näkemisen arvoinen paikka, suosittelen! Myös itse rakennus hieno. Ehkä hieman sokkeloinen rakennus, en ole suinkaan varma tuliko nähtyä kaikki 😁 Löytyy myös kahvila.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: 是个不错的选择，建于1900年，一百多年的建筑和设施到今天都很人性化，对于了解芬兰的历史很有必要！

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Upea, UPEA rakennus. Mukavat näyttelyt. Ainoa häiritsevä asia oli epäselvyys museon kiertämisessä- vasta aivan loppuvaiheilla näimme muutaman kyltin osoittamassa kiertosuuntaa

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Olipas hyvä kokemus. Tällaisena aikana sitä arvostaa itsenäisyyttä ja suomalaisuutta! Akseli Gallen-Kallelan näyttely toi myös monipuolista tietoa taiteilijasta. Lounas oli myös hyvä:)

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
oli mahtava päivä mahtavalle muumi näyttelylle!
suosittelen käymään jos Tove Jansson tai muumit ylipäätänsä kiinnostaa.
muumit 75v. näyttelyssä oli paljon eri ääniefektejä ja videoita seinillä.
lisäksi pieniä laatikoita joissa oli faktoja Tovesta ja hänen urastaan.
lapsiperheille loistava paikka viettää päivää.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Paljon nähtävää ja koettavaa. Lisättyä todellisuutta käytetty havainnollistamaan asioita monipuolisesti.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Sisäänpääsymaksu aikuiselta oli 15e. Alle 18 vuotiaat pääsi ilmaiseksi. Sunnuntaina klo 15 oli ilmainen kierros. Ihan hyvä tapa tutustua museoon. Käymisen arvoinen paikka. En ollut aiemmin käynyt. Kaunis vanha rakennus.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Olen viimeksi käynyt koulun kanssa lapsena Kansallismuseossa ja muutos oli yllättävän suuri. Näyttelyhuoneet ryhmitelty ajan, aiheen mukaan hyvin.
Itämainen näyttely yläkerrassa oli loistava katsaus Lähi-Idän löytöihin.
Parasta oli interaktiivisuus- leikkiä kameran kanssa, kuvilla ja mitä sai aikaan nappeja painamalla - ääntä, liikettä tai aikajana Helsingin asutuksesta.. Suosittelen käyntiä!
Alakerran kahvila-ravintola tarjoaa kelpo ruokaa.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Assolutamente da visitare per capire la storia della Finlandia nella mostra permanente. Molto interattivo e ricco di storia. Stupenda la ricostruzione storica delle case finlandesi in lego. Adatto anche a bambini in età scolare perché tutto è molto interattivo

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Świetne, duże, ciekawe, interaktywne muzeum. Trzeba poświęcić minimum 3 godziny, żeby obejść wszystkie wystawy, ale warto!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Muy grande! La parte de la prehistoria muy chula, tiene algunas cosas interactivas pero al final se hace algo pesado por el exceso de cosas en plan batiburrillo, por lo menos para mi personalmente.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Hieno kokoelma suomen historiaa höystettynä osuvilla faktapläjäyksillä. Ensimmäinen kerta kyseisessä paikassa ja pitää kyllä käydä toisenkin kerran.

Näet "Suomen" rajojen liikkeet vuodesta 1000jkr alkaen jne

Pikku vinkki. Netistä saa liput hieman halvemmalla. Voit myös tehdä itsestäsi "tulevan" presidentin kuvan 😅

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Впечатления от музея вернее от самой показаной истории Финов у меня конечно не фонтан. В музеях истории Казахстана куда интереснее. Фины отличаются скромностью наверное поэтому их золотое наследие просто побрякушки по сравнению с нашим Алтан Адам 😁. Лично меня удивили стенд с фотографиями в которых оживают и  то что даже в музее чувствуется как фины берегут и уважают свою природу  и отношения между друг другом. Жаль не могу прикрепить видео. Очень забавно видеть картину с мигающим старичком. Да и то отличительная черта  скандинавов не врать тоже прослеживается в музее. Для меня это вязаный носок , вернее часть носка уже съедений молью  и обношенный 😁. Больше чем уверена наши связали бы новый 😂😂😂.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Kansallismuseossa Barbi-näyttely! Ennenkuulumatonta! Yleisöä kuitenkin oli ruuhkaksi saakka, kun YLE uutisoi juuri aamulla näyttelystä. Näyttely on auki kansallismuseossa aina elokuu loppuun 2018 saakka.

Näyttelyn hinta, johon kuului myös pääsy vakiyleisnäyttelyyn oli 15€ aikuisilta ja lapset ilmaiseksi. Kulttuuri- ja Lounaskortti (Smartum) käy maksuvälineenä. Barbi-näyttely oli miehellekin mielenkiintoinen kokemus, monia ”vanhoja tuttavuuksia” tuli eteen. Hämmästyttävän hienoja olivat erityisesti julkkisbarbit ja historian merkkihenkilöbarbit. Museon ulkona seisovalla leijonallakin oli barbi-kaulaliina. Aulassa oli esillä iPadillä esitelty barbimeikkausappi, mikä löytyy ilmaiseksi Applelle appstoresta, kun lapset ilmoittavat haluavansa samanlaisen kotiin.

Museon yleisnäyttelyssä oli Suomi eri aikakaudella. Ei jaksanut oikein kiinnostaa enää tytärtä barbi-näyttelyn jälkeen. Pienemmille tuo kahden museon kiertämismahdollisuus meneekin varmasti ohi. Enemmän lapsia tuntui kiinnostavan museon alakerrassa oleva kauppa, josta pystyi ostamaan barbi-kamaa ja muuta Kansallismuseon turistituotteita. Museon tikkarit (1,5€) olivat erityisesti nuorison mieleen.

Kansallismuseoon pääsee helpoiten raitiovaunulla ihan oven eteen. Auto pitää jättää poikkikadulle parkkiin ja kävellä pari korttelia. Pysäköintivyöhyke kallein eli vyöhyke 1. Sunnuntaina pysäköinti maksutonta!!! Museolla ei ole siis mitään pysäköintihallia.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Museet är ganska litet vilket är helt logiskt med tanke på att Finland historia som självständig stat bara sträcker sig drygt hundra år tillbaka. Den permanenta utställningen "Berättelsen om Finland " är mycket sevärd. Museet är definitivt värt ett besök. Det ligger centralt nära den finska riksdagen.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Kansallismuseo Helsingissä on upea rakennus täynnä suomalaisten historiaa satojen vuosien ajalta. Asiaa on paljon, joten jossain vaiheessa kierrosta uupuu. Varaa paljon aikaa tai tule monta kertaa.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Belle extérieur et très Beau plafond, musée assez intéressant, en 2h environ le tour est fait.
La fin de la visite est Très inspirante pour des photographes

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
ヘルシンキ中央駅から徒歩圏内。
歴史ある重厚な建物は外も内も素晴らしいです。
展示内容のボリュームもちょうど良く、駆け足で全部回って1時間ほど。
（もちろんゆっくり周ることをお勧めします）
18歳以下は無料／チケットはオンライン購入が少し安いです。

入口入って右手のクローク（無人）にコートや荷物を預け、手ぶらでゆっくり観てください。
ロッカーは無料。
コイン？が置いてあるので扉を開けて内側にコインを投入し鍵をかけます。
カフェもあり。

注）2023年1月現在、サーミ族関連の展示はなく、全てSIIDA（ラップランド）に所蔵されているとのこと。
少しでも観たかったので残念でした。

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Очень интересный музей, много локаций и экспонатов.
Часто проходят временные выставки с эксклюзивными вещами.
Много интерактивов, с экспонатами можно взаимодействовать.
Очень доброжелательные сотрудники, которые хорошо знают историю, всегда готовы все подробно рассказать.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Мені дуже сподобалось. Була тут вже вдруге. Багато цікавих інтерактивних штук. Моя улюблена це та, де можна заграти на стародавніх інструментах натискаючи великі кола. Це щось неймовірне. Хочу ще і ще грати в ту "гру".

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Tolles Museum! Wir haben genutzt, dass es Freitag von 16-18 Uhr kostenlos ist. Sehr interessante Ausstellungen!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Magnifique musée très dépaysant quand on vient de France.  L'histoire de la Finlande est passionnante et les pièces exposées de pure beauté.  Le lieu même est splendide.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Miejsce warte odwiedzenia. Jako turyści byliśmy zachwyceni wystawami,  elementami interaktywnymi.  Bardzo chętnie  odwiedzimy jeszcze raz.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Todella kiinnostavaa. Kannattaa kyllä käydä, varsinkin jos olet turisti.

Very interesting. Definitely should check out, especially if you're a tourist.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
입장료가 인당16유로로 생각보다 비싸긴했지만
참여적이고 볼거리들이 다양합니다
아이들도 함께 천천히 둘러보며 즐길 수 있는 공간도 많아서 핀란드에 오신 분들은 방문해보시길 바라요

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Questo museo incredibile mostra come la cultura di un popolo possa essere ispirazione per costruire bellezza. E lo fa con la più semplice ed ovvia delle equazioni Arte=religione. Uno potrebbe pensare che questa era una chiesa che è stata trasformata in museo e invece no...è stata costruito come se fosse una chiesa!  Fu iniziato nel 1887 e finito nel 1916..Bellissimi gli affreschi che si trovano nella cupola della volta della navata centrale del pittore finlandese Akseli Gallen-Kallella che ha dipinto scene dalla tradizione epica finlandese...Il museo ospita anche molte mostre temporanee di vario genere....molto interessante..

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Elämyksellinen matka läpi Suomen historian. Videoita, installaatioita, ääniefektejä, historiallisia esineitä, osallistavia tehtäviä. Hienosti toteutettu kokonaisuus! Kannattaa kulkea aikajärjestyksessä salista toiseen ja lukea pohjustava teksti seinältä.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Tuyệt vời. Nhưng có 2 đường cầu thang để lên phòng trưng bày. Đừng bỏ sót.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Molto interessante, una visita piacevole. Tante esposizioni diverse all'interno di un bellissimo spazio.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Приятное место. Сейчас (10.09.20) проходит выставка посвященная Мумии троллям и Твои Ятсон. Для детей очень хорошо преподноситься творчество автора и характеры персонажей.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Lugar incrível. Deve ser visitado. Conta a origem dos povos que viveram na Finlândia até a atual situação política. Ambientes interativos, tais como a galeria dos presentes onde vc pode tirar uma foto e ser incluído como futuro presidente e áudios de bandas de rock. Para as crianças no último andar tem uma sala com jogos interativos. Preço entrada 12€ em 12/2019.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Mielenkiintoinen kokonaisuus, jossa riittää katsottavaa useammallekin käyntikerralle.  Katsottavaa niin lapsille kuin aikuisillekin. Museossa myös myymälä sekä kahvio/ravintola.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Ein ausgesprochenen interessantes Museum zur finnischen Geschichte. Von der Frühzeit bis in die Neuzeit. Spannend aufgebaut und auch für Kinder nicht langweilig. Gut erreichbar. Einfach ein Muss!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Mukavan erilaista taidetta eri saleissa loogisesti järjestettynä. Tilaa kulkea löytyi. Kulkusuuntamerkit hieman epäselviä välillä tai niitä ei näkynyt. Portaita on ihan kiitettävästi.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Sehr schönes Museum mit gelungenen Ausstellungen. Es empfiehlt sich die Audio Tour, da man sonst relativ schnell durch ist.

Freier Eintritt mit Helsinki Card.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Schön gestaltetes und umfangreiches Museum zur finnischen Geschichte (von der Steinzeit bis in die Gegenwart), das sich über drei Etagen erstreckt.
Es sind wirklich viele Ausstellungsstücke zu sehen und es gibt viele Informationen, auch als Audio-Guide.
Die Mitarbeiter sind freundlich und hilfsbereit.
Karten können auch online gebucht werden.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Hieno rakennus niin ulkoa kuin sisältä.

Perusnäyttelyn lisäksi vaihtuvia näyttelyitä.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Museo que habla de la historia de esta ciudad de Estocolmo a lo largo de su historia y la forma en que ha crecido. Muy interesante. Está ubicado cerca del centro de la ciudad.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text:
Kiintoisa näyttely vaurauden saavuttamisen periaatteista n.kymmenen elämässä menestyneen suomalaisen sanoin.

Suomen tarinasta katsoin vain osan. Vuosikuvat lumosivat. Kellarikerroksen kahvilaa suosittelen erityisesti, sen hyvää fiilistä ja ystävällistä palvelua. Kesällä voi kahvitella myös pikkuisella terassilla.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Melkoinen sokkelo ja paljon portaita. Yksi pieni hissi. Menossa remonttiin pariksi vuodeksi.

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Tuttu Helsingin helmi paikka ja olipa mahtavaa tavata erittäin ystävällinen rouvas-työntekijä. Sain paljon tietoo paikasta ja kaikista ihmeellisyyksitä esim, kun vanhakaktus kukkii yli ikkunakaton... on avattu hänen pääsy ulos, jos vain ilma suosii...ihmeellistä huomaavaisuutta henkilöstöltä. Kiitos!!!!!

name: The National Museum of Finland
review_text: Krásné interaktivní muzeum, dá se zde klidně strávit i několik hodin. Projdete Finsko od prehistorie až do roku 2017, kdy slavilo 100 let od svého vzniku. Výstava se Vás snaží, interaktivními prvky (zvuky, filmy, různá tlačítka, světla, stíny,...), vtáhnout do děje. Jsou zde například obrazy prezidentů, když chvilku postojíte a zadíváte se na ně, tak na Vás nějaký mrkne, jiný lehce pokrývá hlavou...do dalšího obrazu budoucího prezidenta se sami vyfotíte. Můžete se pomocí 3D brýlí stát součástí korunovace apod. Úplně nahoře je dílna pro děti, kde se mohou stát mlynářem, pekařem, dělníkem na páse, učitelem, zedníkem, apod.
